com.googlecode.gwt.charts.client

Interface ColumnFunction


  • public interface ColumnFunction
    An interface for providing a calculated function to a DataViewColumn.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Object calc(DataTable dataTable, int row)
      A function that will be called for each row in the column to calculate a value for that cell.

    • Method Detail

      • calc

        Object calc(DataTable dataTable,
          int row)
        A function that will be called for each row in the column to calculate a value for that cell. The function signature is func(dataTable, row), where dataTable is the source DataTable, and row is the index of the source data row. The function should return a single value of the type specified by type.
        Parameters:
        dataTable - is the source DataTable
        row - is the index of the source data row
        Returns:
        should return a single value of the type specified by the column type
